        "timestamp": "2017-09-12 19:45:42.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 6:\n\nJoseph, from my comments below, didn't get answer to some questions, can you provide feedback on these questions below to move forward and put closure on this review from my end?\n\n1. if not covered now, create a jira ticket to remove code duplication in AAI classes, can be future work, now the focus is to get this in the load:\n\ncontrolloop/common/model-impl/aai/src/main/java/org/onap/policy/aai/AAIGETVserverResponse.java\nLine 34:\nIt seems there are vserverID, isClosedLoopDisabled, etc .. is repeated across AAIGET* classes.   It would be better to have a base class with the common fields, ie. AAIGETResponse, and have AAIGETVserverResponse, and others that use these common fields, inherit from it.\n\nLet me know the number.\n\n2. Can these dependencies be removed from pom.xml?\n\ncontrolloop/templates/template.demo.v1.0.0/template.demo/pom.xml\nLine 106:\nThis directory refers to 1.0.0 (will go away as as soon as migrations is possible to 1.1.0).   There should be no changes in this file/directory\n\ncontrolloop/common/eventmanager/pom.xml\nLine 138:\nnot sure why this dependency is needed, I dont see anything introduced in this module related to httpclient, can it be removed?\n\nIf not, as a minimum should be using the same version of the libraries.  These are the recommended ones:\n\n\t\t<http.client.version>4.5.2</http.client.version>\n\t\t<http.core.version>4.4.4</http.core.version>\n\nThank you!",
        "patchset_number": 6
      },
